                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17720909-34-off177 t17720909-34-crimeloc179"></join> on the 7th of September; I saw Litners take a handkerchief out of Hiam's pocket, and give it to Brown; I desired Mr. Gates to take notice of them; which he did. Hiam is a boy; he appeared before the alderman, and swore to his handkerchief, but his father would not let him appear before the grand jury.</p>
